theorem.statement:
Given a bond with stated rate of r_{bond}, nominal rate of r_{nom}maturity (face) value of MV, and 
				which matures in t years with coupons provided m times a year, the purchase price is given by
				MV (1+\frac{r_{nom}}{m})^{-n} + MV \cdot \frac{r_{bond}}{m} \cdot \frac{1-(1+\frac{r_{nom}}{m})^{-n}}{\frac{r_{nom}}{m}}

corollary.statement:
For a bond convertible m times a year and with a yield rate convertible m times a year, if the Face Value is FV and 
				Book Value is BV and Redemption Value is RV, when redeeming immediately after the kth coupon payment yields
					BV = FV \cdot \frac{r_{nom}}{m} \cdot \frac{(1 - (1+\frac{r_{bond}}{m})^{-t \cdot m + k})}{\frac{r_{bond}}{m}} 
						   + RV \cdot (1+\frac{r_{bond}}{m})^{-t \cdot m + k}
